latestPosts.caption:
He wore it like a secret.

A pixelated pendant, small and square, with the shape of a question mark etched where a symbol of certainty might usually be. It looked like something pulled from an old video game—one of those 8-bit mystery boxes that once held power-ups, surprises, second chances.

He liked that it didn’t give answers. That it opened, yes—but not to reveal, not completely. It could hold something: a folded thought, a sliver of memory, or perhaps nothing at all. That was the point.

The locket didn’t explain itself.
It simply asked to be carried.

And so he did—on days when doubt shadowed his steps. When silence felt louder than sound. When he needed to remember that the unknown isn’t always something to fear. That sometimes, the unanswered questions are the ones worth keeping close.

Photography : @dino_image 
Photography asst. : @kirugoescrazy
Creative direction: @dino_image, @smrutimathisekaran 
Muse: @aloshy_amal 
MUA : @artistrybyvankris 
Stylist: @akshara_karimbil

Grateful. Gobsmacked. Glitching with joy. 💥

A huge thank you to @fathima.94 for this pixel-perfect feature on homegrownin!

Who would’ve thought that from shooting campaigns inhouse (yes, literally inside my house — terrace lighting and cousin photographers included), we’d land our first ever out-of-home, out-of-town editorial shoot — and in Kochi, no less.

I packed my bags, boarded a train from Tirunelveli, and showed up nervous but hopeful @Curiousytea. And then… magic happened.

Dino (@dino_image ), our photographer, art director and walking Pinterest board, came in with 100+ art direction ideas for a one-day shoot. I had to play creative referee: “One concept at a time, Dino!” 😅

Van Kris @artistrybyvankris , our makeup wizard,who made sure every look hit just the right nostalgic note.

Swetha (@shwethajayaram_ ), our pageant queen turned pixel goddess, was game for every quirky experiment.

Aloshy (@aloshy_amal ), a dancer who bends gravity like it’s no big deal, brought heart (and a whole lot of limbs) to every frame.

Akshara (@akshara_karimbil ), the stylist who made sure the pixels aligned.. sweet lollies? Check. Love-sick earrings? Check.

And just like that, our 8-Bit Love campaign came alive — a tribute to retro games, love-struck hearts, and the thrill of chasing golden tokens.

From makeshift sets to modular jewels, this was more than a campaign — it was a level-up moment. Thank you all for making it unforgettable. 🎮💛

With love,
Smruti Mathisekaran
